### Design Assets

The design extension provides a structured space for UI/UX thinking, visual references, and aesthetic direction.

Files and folders:

- DESIGN.md  
  A collaborative design document used to define and refine:
  - UI/UX decisions
  - Layout structures and flows
  - Visual style and aesthetic direction
  - Design tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
  - Interaction patterns and behavior

- reference/  
  A folder for visual inputs such as:
  - Screenshots
  - Mockups
  - Inspiration images
  - UI references

- reference/copy.sh  
  A user invoked helper script for copying the latest screenshot into the reference folder for quick iteration.

Guidelines:

- Keep DESIGN.md structured and easy to scan
- Prefer refining existing sections over adding redundant ones
- Use reference/ assets to support decisions in DESIGN.md
- Avoid embedding large images directly in markdown; reference them instead
